name: Handle High CPU usage on Windows
description: This procedure describes how to identify and handle processes on windows, consuming high CPU of the system

steps.description: Login to HOSTNAME using Microsoft RDP or another remote desktop tool

Identify the process that continuously consuming a high amount of CPU

Press the Start button and run the following command:

taskmgr.exe

If the results returned looks like this observing the “Performance” tab there is one or more processes utilizing to much CPU resources.

If not, you can cancel the runbook, indicating that you found the problem and no longer need the runbook.


Select the “Processes” tab and sort the CPU column ascending.


Observing this view for a moment the process CPUSTRES.EXE is constantly close to 100% utilization and the situation does not seem to improve. Enter the name of the process causing stress in your environment as runbook parameter PROCESS_NAME. Continue with the next step.

Attempt to stop the process.

Ensure the PROCESS_NAME process is selected and right-mouse click and select “End Process”.



Confirm that this process should be stopped and continue with the next step.

Check if the problem still exist.

Observing the Task Manager the process should disappear and the CPU utilization should stabilize to a normal level and you can step to the end of the runbook, ignoring all coming steps. Complete the runbook at the end.



Should the process still be active consuming too much CPU resources continue with escalation as described in the last step

Escalate the issue to the next support level

There are other issues with the system needing attention by an engineer. Escalate to the next support level with the information gathered in step 2 above and complete this runbook.
